CNCP v1 23272
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13460: Allow `~/path` as `<img src=\"~/...\">` with `~` alias",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:20:49.362275+00:00",
  "text": "Allow `~/path` as `<img src=\"~/...\">` with `~` alias\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.16\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/OrbisK/vue-img-src-tilde\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `pnpm i`\n2. `pnpm dev`\n3.  Error. The first '~' is always stripped.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe first `~` should not be stripped.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nhttps://github.com/vuejs/core/blob/cdffaf6b9efce2c52635714e8e2d7480737c6b50/packages/compiler-sfc/src/template/templateUtils.ts#L22-L29\n\nThis does always remove the first `~`\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n    OS: Linux 6.8 Ubuntu 24.04.1 LTS 24.04.1 LTS (Noble Numbat)\n    CPU: (8) x64 11th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-1135G7 @ 2.40GHz\n    Memory: 36.29 GB / 62.58 GB\n    Container: Yes\n    Shell: 5.9 - /usr/bin/zsh\n  Binaries:\n    Node: 23.5.0 - ~/.nvm/current/bin/node\n    npm: 10.9.2 - ~/.nvm/current/bin/npm\n    pnpm: 8.15.9 - ~/.nvm/current/bin/pnpm\n    bun: 1.1.42 - ~/.nvm/current/bin/bun\n  Browsers:\n    Chrome: 130.0.6723.69\n  npmPackages:\n    vue: ^3.5.13 => 3.5.16\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nNuxt uses `~` as alias for the `/app` directory.\n\nRef: https://github.com/vitejs/vite-plugin-vue/issues/15\nRef: https://github.com/nuxt/nuxt/pull/32119#issuecomment-2883870331\n\n/cc @danielroe",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
